<h2>Step 5: Connect Google Search Console AI Mode Data</h2>
<p>Google Search Console now separates AI Mode traffic from regular organic search. Connecting GSC to GA4 gives you the full picture.</p>
<p><strong>Specifically:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Open <strong>Google Search Console</strong> for your property</li>
<li>Go to <strong>Performance &gt; Search results</strong></li>
<li>Click <strong>Search Appearance</strong> filter</li>
<li>Select <strong>AI Mode</strong> to see impressions and clicks from Google AI Mode specifically</li>
<li>Compare AI Mode clicks against regular organic clicks for the same queries</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> GA4 cannot distinguish Google AI Mode clicks from regular organic clicks. They both appear as "google / organic." GSC is the only tool that separates them. Google added the <a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/7042828">AI Mode search appearance filter</a> in June 2025. By reviewing both GA4 and GSC data together, you see the complete AI traffic picture.</p>
